main

public static final void main(java.lang.String[] args)
Deprecated. 
The behavior of the main() method is important because this is one of the classes that can be launched from the "iiq" script via the Launcher class.

One argument is expected which is a string of clear text to be encrypted. The encryption of this string is printed.

If you need to add other test methods, you could do this with - flags.
